'''John Momoh''' (born on July 1, 1954) is a Nigerian [[broadcast journalist]] and the Chairman and CEO of [[Channels TV]], an independent and multiple award winning 24-hour [[news channel|news]] and media [[television channel]] based in Lagos, Nigeria.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://businessdayonline.com/2014/05/john-momoh-frowns-at-media-for-idolising-ex-convicts/#.VKY7RSvF81M | title=John Momoh frowns at media for idolising ex-convicts | publisher=[[Business Day (Nigeria)|Business Day]] | date=6 May 2014 | accessdate=2 January 2015 | author=Obi, Daniel}}</ref>. He is widely recognized in Nigeria as a transformative industry pioneer with the distinguished career in news [[television broadcasting]].

==Early life and education==

John Momoh graduated from the [[University of Lagos]] with a Bachelor degree in Mass Communication and a Master<U+2019>s degree in International Law and Diplomacy. In June 2013, he received the [[Lagos Business School]]<U+2019>s ''Distinguished Alumni Award''.

John Momoh has professional Diplomas from the UK<U+2019>s [[Thomson Foundation]] and the [[University of Manchester]], is an alumnus of the prestigious [[Harvard Business School]] and a Fellow of the Nigerian Guild of Editors and the [[Nigerian Institute of Journalism]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://leadership.ng/news/356784/national-conference-media-must-remain-observers-momoh | title=National Conference: Media must remain Observers <U+2013> Momoh | publisher=[[Leadership (Nigeria)|Leadership]] | date=18 March 2014 | accessdate=2 January 2015}}</ref>

==Career==

Prior to starting Channels Television, which he co-founded in 1992, John worked variously as News Anchor, Senior Reporter and Senior Producer for Nigeria<U+2019>s National Radio and Television Stations, Radio Nigeria and the Nigerian Television Authority.

==Awards and recognition==

In December 2005, he was proclaimed "Officer of the Order of the Niger" by the [[Government of Nigeria|Nigerian Government]].<ref name="ls1">{{cite web | url=http://leadership.ng/news/388585/john-momoh-receive-prestigious-leadership-award-canada | title=John Momoh To Receive Prestigious Leadership Award In Canada | publisher=Leadership | date=29 October 2014 | accessdate=2 January 2015 | author=Okojie, George}}</ref>

In 2006, he was honoured with a ''Lifetime Achievement Award'' by the Nigerian Information Society and, two years later, he was nominated as Nigeria<U+2019>s ''Entrepreneur of the Year'' by the Fate Foundation.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.channelstv.com/2014/11/01/john-momoh-receive-prestigious-leadership-award-canada/ | title=John Momoh To Receive Prestigious Leadership Award In Canada | publisher=[[Channels TV]] | date=1 November 2014 | accessdate=2 January 2015}}</ref>

In Novebmer 2014, John Momoh was honoured the ''Leadership Award'' at the 2014 Planet Africa Awards held at the Grand Victorian Convention Centre in Canada.<ref name="ls1"/>

He is a Fellow of The International Visitor Programme (IVP), an initiative of the [[United States Information Agency]], a "Chevening" Fellow and a Fellow of the "African Future Leaders", both initiatives of the [[Government of the United Kingdom|British Government<U+2019>s]] Foreign and Commonwealth Office.

